item.title: New Build?
item.dc:creator: @mwiebelhaus mwiebelhaus
item.description:
@mwiebelhaus wrote:

Or a Antec 300. That case is ugly, get something that looks a bit profressional. Antec 300 is $50 and good, there are other cases that are better than the Antec 300 too and a lot less that 170 dollars. Ill look for some in a second. No everything you buy has to be from newegg. I have only good experinces with Dell monitors. How are you going to buy that monitor? Im not sure they sell deactived items…so get this one http://accessories.us.dell.com/sna/products/Displays/productdetail.aspx?c=us&l=en&s=dhs&cs=19&sku=320-8299 looks better same price 23 inches vs 21.5 same features but better brand and better style. 159.99 for a 1tb harddrive wow thats fucking ridiculious, does anyone do their research anymore? Spend 40 more dollars and get this green drive. http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16822136344&cm_re=2tb_hard_drive--22-136-344--Product I have the 500 gb version and you cant even hear it. If you think the 5400 rmp vs the 7200rmp is going to offer a difference in performance then your on crack because I have 3 computers with western digital black harddrives (320gb) that spin at 7200 rpm and this computer I just built with a green harddrive 5200rpm has no notable performance differences that the harddrives that spin at 7200 rpm. 9800GTX ? get a better card and make it future proof. Honestly SLI means that the card you currently have is getting old and you need to add another one to get better performance. http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16814130476&cm_re=gtx_275--14-130-476--Product the motherboard is deactivated also. Honestly im not even going to waste my time on this now…the cooler is a pos…who uses pin coolers unless you are using the free stock cooler.

Read full topic
